---
name: Agent workflow pattern
description: Coordinator model - record tasks, spawn background agents, never block chat. Verification agent follows every task agent.
type: feedback
---

All work runs through background agents. Claude stays as coordinator — records tasks, talks to user, spawns agents.

**Why:** User does not want chat hold-ups. Foreground agents block the coordinator and make it unresponsive.

**How to apply:**
1. Record every task in the todo list
2. Spawn a **task agent** in background to do the work
3. When task agent completes, immediately spawn a **verification agent** in background to check for upstream/downstream breakage, regressions, and consistency
4. Report results from both agents as they come in
5. Log every completed task to the work area's `record-log.md` (e.g. `v2/orchestrators/_workspace/canonical/record-log.md`) with date and summary
6. Never block the chat waiting on an agent — stay responsive for new tasks at all times
